More and more forces are mobilized for giant strik
The League of Trade Unions and the Hungarian Federation of Trade Unions will form their coordination committee on Friday for the indefinite duration of the strike beginning on Monday.
On Saturday a large protest assembly will be held, on Monday - on the day of the referendum on the Health Insurance Act - the work stoppage begins.
It is expected that there will be significant traffic obstacles due to strikes, as rail transport is almost completely stopped, and the Budapest public transport companies (BKV) will also be on strike until 1 p.m.
Details of the strike on Monday will be announced jointly by the League of Trade Unions and the Trade Union Federation on Friday afternoon.
A LIGA - MOSZ strike committee is also set up, which is responsible for coordinating the actions on Monday.
On Saturday, a large protest assembly will be held, and from Monday on, all organizations that have joined the strike will put down the work for an indefinite period of time, unless agreement is reached with the government.
In other words, the end of the strike, which began on the day of the parliamentary vote on the Health Insurance Act, was not defined.
If the National Council does not accept the Health Insurance Act, the unions immediately withdraw the call for strike.
However, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet to discuss how to proceed.
