Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of production of the driver's licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even harder to find the right vehicle insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding severance payment in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is composed of several factors, including age, sex, the time when the driving licence is drawn up, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, who, according to statistical data and therefore also to the firm's conviction, tend to suffer fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit of the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequently the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance must take account of a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points that should be considered when selecting an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
Under 25-year-olds face numerous obstacles when choosing a low-cost insurance policy, such as low driving practice and a young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to complete a comprehensive insurance, there are nevertheless cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can select a full-scale with excess, so that the services of a full-scale insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is fixed before the contract is concluded and the amount of the insurance premium is higher than the sum to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by the own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs, so your credit will increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. This is due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for a fully comprehensive insurance with excess.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their experience so far, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish leader of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the beginner's fear has been discarded.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable to take out comprehensive insurance for a married customer who does not have children; of course only if the financial situation of the relevant person permits it.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full insurance with excess (with an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In the case that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance, which will only be used for the third year of the vehicle, is recommended.
Luis Noguera notes that they drive more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to pay a higher contribution.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full insurance with excess (with an amount of 150 euros) or an extended insurance, which will only apply if a sufficiently high credit is credited.
Finally, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs that require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
